com.rath.rathbot.cmd

Class RBCommand

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.rath.rathbot.cmd.RBCommand
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    FAQCmd, FAQEditCmd, FAQListCmd, FAQRemoveCmd, HelpCmd, MuteCmd, ReportCmd, UIDCmd, UnmuteCmd

    public abstract class RBCommand
extends java.lang.Object
    This class forms the skeleton of a command. In addition to the abstract methods here, you *must* override the executeCommand() method. See the template at the bottom of this file for details.
    Author:
    Tim Backus tbackus127@gmail.com

      • permissionLevelRequired

        public abstract int permissionLevelRequired()
        The permission level of the issuer that must be met or exceeded for the command to execute.
        Returns:
        the permission level as an int. Permission constants are declared in the RBCommand class.

      • requiresDirectMessage

        public abstract boolean requiresDirectMessage()
        Whether or not the command can only be issued through a direct message to RathBot.
        Returns:
        true if it needs a DM; false if not.

      • setupCommand

        public void setupCommand()
        Performs various initialization operations for commands, such as loading data from a file, building tables, or anything else necessary to execute before the command can be issued. If no setup is required, overriding this method is unnecessary.

      • getSubcommands

        public java.util.Set<RBCommand> getSubcommands()
        Gets the sub-commands this command has. Override this method if your command has sub-commands.
        Returns:
        a Set of RBCommand classes. Use a HashSet for these, not a TreeSet.

      • executeCommand

        public boolean executeCommand(sx.blah.discord.handle.obj.IUser author,
                              sx.blah.discord.handle.obj.IChannel channel,
                              java.lang.String[] tokens,
                              int tokenDepth)
        Executes the command. Any external data needed must first be added to the child command's class via other non-inherited methods. See /ref/templates.txt for instructions to correctly override this method.
        Parameters:
        author - the IUser that executed the command.
        channel - the channel the command was received from.
        tokens - an array of Strings that were split at commas.
        tokenDepth - the index of the token we are working with.
        Returns:
        true if the recursive command search can be stopped; false if not.

      • checkSubcommands

        protected static final RBCommand checkSubcommands(java.util.Set<RBCommand> subcommands,
                                                  java.lang.String[] tokens,
                                                  int tokenDepth)
        Checks the command's subcommands against the given tokens for a command name match.
        Parameters:
        subcommands - the command's subcommands.
        tokens - the tokens in the author's message.
        tokenDepth - which token we're checking.
        Returns:
        the RBCommand that matches the token; null if nothing matches.
